Fill and boil your #kettle{} and preheat your #oven{} to 220°C.

Pop the @British Honey Mustard Sausages{4} on a #baking tray{} and roast them on the top shelf of your oven until browned and cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}, turning halfway through cooking.

> IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Pop them in a large #saucepan{} along with @salt{1/2%tsp}, cover with boiling water and put onto high heat. Boil the potatoes until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a small #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the onion and cook until softened and beginning to brown, ~{5-7%minutes}. Stir often.

> This is the base of your gravy.

When the potatoes have 5 mins left, add the @chopped cavolo nero{100} to the pan of potatoes. Submerge the cavolo nero in the boiling water or cover with a #lid{} so it cooks. Cook until tender, ~{5%minutes}.

Lower the heat of the pan with the onions to medium and add the @balsamic vinegar{12}. Cook until almost evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @water for the sauce{75} to the pan and bring to the boil. Stir in the @red wine stock paste{28} and @redcurrant jelly{25} to dissolve. Simmer for ~{2-3%minutes} until the sauce has thickened slightly.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Meanwhile, drain the potatoes and cavolo nero in a #colander{} then return to the pan. Mash together with a #potato masher{} and then mix in the @wholegrain mustard{1} and a knob of @?butter{}(if you have some). Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} - colcannon made!

Share the colcannon between your plates and serve the sausages alongside. Spoon the gravy over the sausages and tuck in!